        <description>
            <geninfo>
                <para>The moisture drain tubes on the engine compartment evaporator/heater duct perform several
                    important functions by allowing moisture to leave the duct and preventing dirt and debris from
                    entering. There have been some reports of these tubes becoming hard, cracking, or missing. If you
                    see a vehicle that has a drain tube cracked or missing, it is important that the tube be replaced to
                    prevent dirt and debris from entering and causing damage to the system. There has been a change to
                    the drain tube material to prevent this failure. The new material went into production on July 1,
                    2003 for all models.
                </para>
            </geninfo>
        </description>
